  "doc_id": "36511",
  "text": "The transducer presented herein, thanks to its particularly shaped polymeric encapsulation and its broad range of actuation frequencies, can be effectively employed for the development of tactile displays suitable to different application scenarios. This encapsulated piezoelectric transducer can be integrated within tactile displays for sensory substitution to assist the blind or visually-impaired, deaf or hearing-impaired, and combined sensory impaired (deaf-blind) individuals. Several examples can be found in the literature about tactile aids used to convey the information coming from one sensory channel to the tactile sense in a perceptible manner [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [5] [CITATION_3] 49] .",
